{"title_page": "Aramide (musician)", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Aramide\n| image = \n| image_size = 220px\n| landscape = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt = \n| caption =\n| background = solo_singer\n| birth_name = Aramide Sarumoh\n| native_name = Aramide\n| native_name_lang = \n| alias = \n| birth_date = 22 June\n| birth_place = [[Nigeria]]\n| origin = [[Ibadan]], Nigeria\n| death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date 1st) -->\n| death_place = \n| genre = {{hlist|[[Afro-soul]]| [[jazz]]}}\n| occupation = {{hlist|Singer| songwriter}}\n| instrument = {{hlist|[[Saxophone]]| [[guitar]]}}\n| years_active = 2011-present\n| label = Arry Moore\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[eLDee]]| [[Adekunle Gold]]|[[Skales]]|Saeon}}\n| website = {{URL|www.aramidemusic.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Aramide Sarumoh''', (born 22 June),<ref>{{cite web|title=Aramide celebrates birthday with colourful photos|url=http://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2016/06/22/aramide-celebrates-birthday-with-colourful-photos/|website=PM News Nigeria|accessdate=9 July 2016}}</ref> known professionally as '''Aramide''', is a Nigerian [[Afro-soul]] singer and songwriter.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aramide Biography|url=http://aramidemusic.com/bio|publisher=Aramide|accessdate=}}</ref> She won Best Vocal Performance (Female) for \"Iwo Nikan\" at the [[The Headies 2015|Headies 2015]].<ref name=\"Full list of winners @ The Headies 2015\">{{cite news|title=Full list of winners @ The Headies 2015|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2016/01/full-list-of-winners-the-headies-2015/|date=2 January 2016}}</ref> She graduated with a [[political science]] degree from the [[University of Jos]]. \n<br/> In 2019, Aramide was appointed by [[The Recording Academy]] as a Board of Governor for the Washington, D.C. Chapter of the Academy.<ref name=\"Aramide appointed Chapter Governor\">{{cite news|title=Aramide appointed by the The Recording Academy (the GRAMMYs\u00ae) as a Board of Governor for the Washington, D.C. Chapter|url=https://www.aramidemusic.com/home/blog/aramide-appointed-by-the-the-recording-academy-the-grammys-as-a-board-of-governor-for-the-washingt|date=16 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\n\n===Personal life===\nAramide is married. Her traditional marriage and white wedding were held on 18 April 2015 in her hometown, [[Ibadan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Popular Singer, Aramide Ties The Knot With Her Husband (Photos) - Gistmania|url=http://www.gistmania.com/talk/topic,256176.0.html|accessdate=9 July 2016|work=www.gistmania.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=More PHOTOS: Singer Aramide's church wedding|url=http://africanspotlight.com/2015/04/18/more-photos-singer-aramides-church-wedding/|accessdate=9 July 2016|work=African Spotlight|date=18 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Being married cannot slow down my career \u2014 Aramide - Vanguard News|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/09/being-married-cannot-slow-down-my-career-aramide/|accessdate=9 July 2016|date=4 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Music career and breakthrough single==\nAramide's music quest started in 2006, when she contested on \u2018Star Quest\u2019 one of Nigeria\u2019s most prestigious and competitive music talent hunt shows. Her band did very well in the competition as they were judged the 3rd Runners Up. In 2008, she was a part of a show called \u2018Divas Unplugged\u2019 in the famous city of Jos in Nigeria; the show had all the leading female artistes in the Nigerian music industry and her participation in this show was very challenging and rewarding, and her performance and involvement was very inspirational.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aramide was on star Quest|url=http://praisemama.com/artists/aramide/|accessdate=12 July 2016}}</ref> On September 9, 2014 she got signed to Baseline Music after exiting from Trybe Records.<ref>{{cite web|title=Singer Aramide Signs a New Record Label Deal with Baseline Music After Trybe Records Exit|url=http://www.kokovibes.com.ng/2014/09/singer-aramide-signs-new-record-label.html|accessdate=9 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Aramide Joins Skales And Saeon At Baseline Music|url=http://thenet.ng/2014/09/aramide-joins-skales-and-saeon-at-baseline-music/|accessdate=9 July 2016|date=9 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161125122657/http://thenet.ng/2014/09/aramide-joins-skales-and-saeon-at-baseline-music/|archive-date=25 November 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Iwo Nikan===\nOn February 4, 2015 Aramide released her first single under Baseline Music, \"Iwo Nikan\", which ended up not just being a single but a breakthrough for her and the label Baseline Music. She won Best Vocal Performance for the same song \"Iwo Nikan\" at [[The Headies 2015|The Headies]] Award 2015.\n\n===Musical influence and genres===\nAramide's music is influenced by [[Erykah Badu]], [[Miriam Makeba]], [[Sade (singer)|Sade]], and [[Ang\u00e9lique Kidjo]]. Aramide fuses [[soul (music)|soul]] and [[jazz]] with [[African music]] to depict her sound.<ref>{{cite web|title=10 Things You Didn't Know About Aramide|url=http://youthvillageng.com/10-things-you-didnt-know-about-aramide/|website=Youth Village Nigeria|accessdate=9 July 2016|date=5 April 2016}}</ref> She performs in Yoruba and English, and is known for her style, which she calls [[Afro-Soul]].\n\n===''Suitcase''===\nAramide's debut album ''Suitcase'' was released November 22, 2016. It features features guest appearances from [[Sound Sultan]], [[Ice Prince]], [[Adekunle Gold]], [[Koker (singer)|Koker]] and Sir Dauda. The album was produced by Cobhams, Laitan Dada, Sizzle Pro and Tintin.<ref>{{cite web|title=Suitcase by Aramide on Itunes|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ng/album/suitcase/id1175242398||accessdate=20 September 2017|date=22 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Aramide Suitcase Live (ASL)===\nAramide embarked on a debut tour and showcased her album in the United States, Ghana, Nigeria, Canada and other countries. The tour was titled \"Aramide Suitcase Live\" (ASL).\n\n===Songversation With Aramide (SWA)===\nSongversation With Aramide is an initiative of Afro-Soul/Jazz musician Aramide. The event, which is in its second year, is held annually to mark the International Women's Day through the promotion of positive narratives for Nigerian women.\n\nAs a concert-style event, it blends music with topical conversation to motivate women to take the lead, foster personal development and gain societal recognition. The event, also celebrates the achievements of women who have made impact in the unique fields.\n\nWith featured performances from Aramide and other artistes, the event highlights the power of music in championing the goals of women.\n\n==Notable Performances and Songs==\nShe has been performing in several popular events and shows since she rose to stardom in United Kingdom, Canada, Dubai, Nigeria, Ghana etc.:<ref>{{cite web|title=Aramide - Shows|url=http://aramidemusic.com/bio|website=Aramide|accessdate=9 July 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Aramide's performances\">{{cite news|title=Aramide To Perform At One Africa Music FEST|url=https://www.vibe.com/2017/08/one-africa-music-fest-nyc-recap/|accessdate=20 September 2017|date=15 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n===As lead artist===\nList of Aramide's singles as lead artist before debut Album <ref>{{cite web|title=Aramide songs on iTunes|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/aramide/id584867864|website=iTunes|accessdate=9 July 2016}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Killing Me\"\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2011\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"It\u2019s Over\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Feeling This Feeling\"\n|2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Iwo Nikan\"\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2015\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Odun Tuntun\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"I Don't Care\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Love Me\"\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2016\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"FunMi Lowo\"\n|}\n\nHer single \"I Don\u2019t Care\" was spotted on number 1 spot on [[MTN Group|MTN Yhello Top 10]] Nigeria Chart, number 4 on Alternative Music Naija Chart on Top Radio 90.9 FM and number 3 on Alternative Nigeria Chart on Radio Continental 102.3FM.<ref name=\"Aramide is to perform at Fellabration\">{{cite news|title=Aramide To Perform At Felabration|url=http://lifestyle.ng/aramide-to-perform-at-felabration/|accessdate=9 July 2016|work=LifeStyle.ng|date=15 October 2015}}</ref> Also \"Love Me\" picked on number 1 spot on Alternative Nigerian Chart on [[The Beat 99.9 FM]] <ref>{{cite web|title=Alternative Nigerian Chart {{!}} The Beat 99.9 FM|url=http://www.thebeat99.com/chart/alternative-nigerian-06-04-2016|website=The Beat 99.9 Fm|accessdate=9 July 2016}}</ref> and on number 3 spot on Playdata Chart.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Irede|first1=Princess|title=Playdata Radio Chart: Top 10 songs on Nigerian radio [Week 9]|url=http://pulse.ng/buzz/playdata-radio-chart-top-10-songs-on-nigerian-radio-week-9-id4776042.html|website=Pulse Nigeria|accessdate=9 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2015\u201316)\n! scope=\"col\"| Song\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n|[[MTN Group|MTN Yhello Top 10]] Nigeria \n|rowspan=\"3\"|\"I Don't Care\"\n|1\n|-\n|Top Radio 90.9 FM\n|4\n|-\n|Radio Continental 102.3FM\n|3\n|-\n|[[The Beat 99.9 FM]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|\"Love Me\"\n|1\n|-\n|Playdata Chart\n|3\n|-\n|[[The Beat 99.9 FM]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|\"FunMi Lowo\"\n|1\n|-\n|Playdata Chart\n|10\n|}\n\n===As Featured artist===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles as featured artist\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:20em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Artist Name(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Falling\" <small> (featuring. [[Faze (musician)|Faze]] & Aramide) </small>\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Femi Jubal\"\n|2011\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Fever\" <small> (featuring. Aramide, [[Yemi